      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🔴 Critical] Line 202: The new shared `seenWakeupIds` cache deduplicates calls and message/invite wakeups using only `to:key:id`. This means a previously seen message/invite value can suppress a later call wakeup if the same scoped DHT id is reused or collides. Previously, non-call values could not poison call dedupe. Since the consequence is missing a call wakeup, keep call and message dedupe domains separate by including the wakeup kind in the key or by using separate caches.\n```suggestion\nval dedupeKind \u003d if (isCall) \"call\" else \"message\"\nseenWakeupIds.put(\"$scope:$dedupeKind:$id\", Unit) \u003d\u003d null\n```",
      "revId": "bc3219060f3d4992cddd3dbf7f1fba85d3940650",
